    ]
  },
  sections: [{
    properties: { page: { margin: { top: 1440, right: 1440, bottom: 1440, left: 1440 } } },
    children: [
      // Subject line
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun({ text: "Subject: ", bold: true }),
          new TextRun("Eastpoint Capital + AutomateFlow — an honest conversation")
        ]
      }),

      // Greeting
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [new TextRun("Mr. Eastpoint,")]
      }),

      // Opening - acknowledge the gap
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun("I want to be direct with you. You asked us for references from firms like yours — collection law firms using AutomateFlow. We've spent the past two weeks reaching out to every similar account we could find, and we haven't been able to deliver what you asked for.")
        ]
      }),

      // Why the gap exists
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun("That's not because AutomateFlow doesn't work for legal operations — it does. It's because the firms we've found either aren't far enough into their implementations to speak to results, or the contacts aren't available. I could give you a reference from a medical supply company or a marketing agency, but you were clear that wouldn't be useful. I respect that.")
        ]
      }),

      // The pivot
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun({ text: "So let me be clear about what we are and what we're not.", bold: true })
        ]
      }),

      // What we're not
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun({ text: "We are not a legal-specific tool.", bold: true }),
          new TextRun(" We don't have a product built exclusively for collection law firms. If that's what you need — a vendor who only does legal and has a hundred references in your exact industry — we're not that, and I won't pretend otherwise.")
        ]
      }),

      // What we are
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun({ text: "What we are is an automation platform that your team has already validated.", bold: true }),
          new TextRun(" Charles, Corey, and Sayde have spent weeks mapping your processes, and the technical approach is sound. The e-filing mandate isn't going away. Power Automate is failing 3-4 times a week with no one watching. Your clients are asking why this isn't automated yet.")
        ]
      }),

      // What's been proven
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 120 },
        children: [new TextRun("What we've proven so far:")]
      }),
      new Paragraph({
        numbering: { reference: "bullet-list", level: 0 },
        spacing: { after: 80 },
        children: [new TextRun("Corey — who built your Word merge system — validated our approach: pick up completed docs from the merge folder, push to PandaDoc, route for signature. No need to recreate complex templates.")]
      }),
      new Paragraph({
        numbering: { reference: "bullet-list", level: 0 },
        spacing: { after: 80 },
        children: [new TextRun("We built a working webhook-to-PandaDoc integration in the first session with Charles.")]
      }),
      new Paragraph({
        numbering: { reference: "bullet-list", level: 0 },
        spacing: { after: 80 },
        children: [new TextRun("We've identified 10+ use cases worth an estimated $230K/year in efficiency gains across your departments.")]
      }),
      new Paragraph({
        numbering: { reference: "bullet-list", level: 0 },
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [new TextRun("Even basic failure alerting — knowing when something breaks before it compounds — would be a win your team doesn't have today.")]
      }),

      // The line in the sand
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun({ text: "Here's my honest question:", bold: true }),
          new TextRun(" Is the lack of a legal-specific reference a dealbreaker? Or is it enough that your own people — Charles, Corey, the department heads who've seen this — believe it James work?")
        ]
      }),

      // The choice
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun("I'm not trying to pressure you. You've built something worth protecting, and I understand the instinct to be careful. But if the standard is \"perfect industry match or nothing,\" we won't be able to meet it — and I'd rather tell you that now than waste more of your team's time.")
        ]
      }),

      // Close
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun("If internal validation from Charles, Corey, and your managers is enough to move forward, we're ready. If it's not, I understand, and I wish you well finding the right solution.")
        ]
      }),

      // CTA
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 200 },
        children: [
          new TextRun("Would you be open to a brief call to discuss? I'd rather hear your thinking directly than guess at it.")
        ]
      }),

      // Sign off
      new Paragraph({
        spacing: { after: 80 },
        children: [new TextRun("Regards,")]
      }),
      new Paragraph({
        children: [new TextRun("Kurt")]
      }),
      new Paragraph({
        children: [new TextRun({ text: "Legal Counsel, AutomateFlow", italics: true })]
      })
    ]
  }]
});

